<h2 class="sectionedit1"><a name="standard_types_and_their_properties" id="standard_types_and_their_properties">Standard types and their properties</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

</div>
<!-- EDIT1 SECTION "Standard types and their properties" [1-47] -->
<h3 class="sectionedit2"><a name="types" id="types">Types</a></h3>
<div class="level3">

<p>

In <code>&lt;stddef&gt;</code> header:

</p>
<div class="table sectionedit3"><table class="inline">
	<tr class="row0">
		<td class="col0 leftalign"> <code>ptrdiff_t</code>  </td><td class="col1"> signed integer type returned after substracting two pointers </td>
	</tr>
	<tr class="row1">
		<td class="col0 leftalign"> <code>size_t</code>     </td><td class="col1"> unsigned integer type returned by <code>sizeof</code> </td>
	</tr>
	<tr class="row2">
		<td class="col0 leftalign"> <code>nullptr_t</code>  </td><td class="col1"> the type of <code>NULL</code> pointer object (<code>nullptr</code>) (<a href="../c_0x" class="wikilink1" title="c_0x">C++0x</a> feature)</td>
	</tr>
	<tr class="row3">
		<td class="col0"> <code>max_align_t</code></td><td class="col1"> the type which has the alignment supported in every context (<a href="../c_0x" class="wikilink1" title="c_0x">C++0x</a> feature) </td>
	</tr>
</table></div>
<!-- EDIT3 TABLE [88-428] -->
<p>

Also, several <a href="integer" class="wikilink1" title="types:integer"> fixed width integer types </a> are defined to enhance portability of applications (<a href="../c_0x" class="wikilink1" title="c_0x">C++0x</a> feature) 
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT2 SECTION "Types" [48-558] -->
<h3 class="sectionedit4"><a name="numeric_limits" id="numeric_limits">Numeric limits</a></h3>
<div class="level3">

<p>

The <a href="limits" class="wikilink1" title="types:limits"> numeric_limits</a> class template defines common implementation-defined properties of fundamental types.
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT4 SECTION "Numeric limits" [559-701] -->
<h3 class="sectionedit5"><a name="macro_constants" id="macro_constants">Macro constants</a></h3>
<div class="level3">

<p>

In <code>&lt;cstdint&gt;</code> header:

</p>
<div class="table sectionedit6"><table class="inline">
	<tr class="row0">
		<td class="col0"> <code>PTRDIFF_MIN</code> </td><td class="col1"> minimum value of object of <code>ptrdiff_t</code> type (<a href="../c_0x" class="wikilink1" title="c_0x">C++0x</a> feature) </td>
	</tr>
	<tr class="row1">
		<td class="col0"> <code>PTRDIFF_MAX</code> </td><td class="col1"> maximum value of object of <code>ptrdiff_t</code> type (<a href="../c_0x" class="wikilink1" title="c_0x">C++0x</a> feature) </td>
	</tr>
	<tr class="row2">
		<td class="col0 leftalign"> <code>SIZE_MAX</code>    </td><td class="col1"> maximum value of object of <code>size_t</code> type (<a href="../c_0x" class="wikilink1" title="c_0x">C++0x</a> feature) </td>
	</tr>
</table></div>
<!-- EDIT6 TABLE [753-1016] -->
<p>

